---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/layout/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What is FIRE? — Financial Independence, Retire Early Explained"
  description="Learn what FIRE means, how it works, and why millions of people are pursuing financial independence and early retirement. Complete guide to the FIRE movement."
  canonical="https://tools.devsahil.com/learn/what-is-fire"
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-hairline bg-canvas py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Learn</p>
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          What is FIRE?
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-body">Financial Independence, Retire Early — a movement transforming how people think about work and money.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article class="bg-canvas py-12 sm:py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none space-y-8 text-body">
          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The FIRE Movement Explained</h2>
            <p>FIRE stands for <strong>Financial Independence, Retire Early</strong>. It's a lifestyle movement focused on aggressive saving and investing to achieve financial freedom well before the traditional retirement age of 65.</p>
            <p>At its core, FIRE is about gaining control over your time by accumulating enough wealth that work becomes optional. Instead of working for 40+ years and retiring at 65, FIRE practitioners aim to retire in their 30s, 40s, or 50s.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The Core Principles</h2>
            <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">1. Save Aggressively</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Most FIRE practitioners save 50-70% of their income, compared to the typical 10-20% savings rate.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">2. Invest Wisely</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Put your savings to work through index funds, real estate, or other growth investments.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">3. Reduce Expenses</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Cut unnecessary spending and focus on what truly brings you happiness.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas-soft p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">4. Increase Income</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Side hustles, career growth, and multiple income streams accelerate your journey.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The 4% Rule</h2>
            <p>The most common FIRE calculation uses the <strong>4% Rule</strong> (also known as the Safe Withdrawal Rate). This rule states that you can safely withdraw 4% of your portfolio annually in retirement without running out of money.</p>
            <p>This means if you need $40,000 per year to live, you need $1,000,000 invested (40,000 ÷ 0.04 = 1,000,000). The rule is based on the Trinity Study, which found that a 4% withdrawal rate had a high success rate over 30-year periods.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The FIRE Number</h2>
            <p>Your <strong>FIRE Number</strong> is the amount of money you need to retire early. It's typically calculated as:</p>
            <div class="rounded-lg bg-canvas-soft-2 p-4 font-mono text-sm text-ink">
              FIRE Number = Annual Expenses × 25
            </div>
            <p>For example, if you spend $50,000 per year, your FIRE Number is $1,250,000. For a more conservative approach (Fat FIRE), multiply by 30 instead of 25.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Types of FIRE</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Lean FIRE</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Requires 20× annual expenses. Focuses on minimalist living with lower expenses. Often involves geographic arbitrage or a simpler lifestyle.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border-2 border-ink bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Regular FIRE</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Requires 25× annual expenses. Maintains a comfortable middle-class lifestyle without major sacrifices.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Fat FIRE</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Requires 30× annual expenses. For those who want to maintain a higher standard of living in retirement.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Coast FIRE</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Save enough early that compound interest will grow your portfolio to your retirement number. You can then work optional jobs or take lower-stress positions.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Is FIRE Right for You?</h2>
            <p>FIRE isn't for everyone, but it offers valuable principles regardless of your goals:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-body">
              <li>Financial security and freedom of choice</li>
              <li>Reduced stress about money and job security</li>
              <li>More time for family, hobbies, and passions</li>
              <li>The ability to pursue meaningful work without financial pressure</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-lg bg-canvas-soft-2 p-6">
            <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Ready to Calculate Your FIRE Number?</h2>
            <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-body">Use our free calculator to see how close you are to financial independence.</p>
            <a
              href="/calculator"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-ink px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
            >
              Open Calculator
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
